<div class="container eye-container1">
    <h2 class="text-center mb-3">Eye Care Information</h2>
    <div class="accordion accordion-flush mt-4" id="accordionExample">
        <div class="accordion-item">
            <h2 class="accordion-header">
                <button class="accordion-button collapsed main-btn fs-4 p-3 rounded"
                        type="button"
                        data-bs-toggle="collapse"
                        data-bs-target="#collapseOne"
                        aria-expanded="false"
                        aria-controls="collapseOne">
                    Eye Care and Preventative Measures
                </button>
            </h2>
            <div id="collapseOne"
                 class="accordion-collapse collapse"
                 data-bs-parent="#accordionExample">
                <div class="accordion-body">
                    Taking proactive steps to care for your eyes is crucial for
                    maintaining optimal vision and preventing potential eye
                    conditions. Regular eye exams are fundamental; they can detect
                    early signs of diseases such as glaucoma, cataracts, and macular
                    degeneration before noticeable symptoms emerge. An annual check-up
                    allows eye care professionals to monitor changes in vision and
                    adjust prescriptions for glasses or contact lenses accordingly.
                    Moreover, adopting a diet rich in omega-3 fatty acids, vitamins C
                    and E, and zinc can support eye health. Foods like leafy greens,
                    fish, nuts, and citrus fruits provide essential nutrients that
                    help protect against age-related vision issues.
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
        <div class="accordion-item">
            <h2 class="accordion-header">
                <button class="accordion-button collapsed main-btn fs-4 p-3 rounded"
                        type="button"
                        data-bs-toggle="collapse"
                        data-bs-target="#collapseTwo"
                        aria-expanded="false"
                        aria-controls="collapseTwo">
                    Protecting Your Eyes from Digital Strain
                </button>
            </h2>
            <div id="collapseTwo"
                 class="accordion-collapse collapse"
                 data-bs-parent="#accordionExample">
                <div class="accordion-body">
                    In today's digital age, many people spend extended periods staring
                    at screens, which can lead to digital eye strain or computer
                    vision syndrome. Symptoms include dry eyes, headaches, blurred
                    vision, and neck and shoulder pain. To mitigate these effects, the
                    20-20-20 rule is highly recommended: every 20 minutes, take a
                    20-second break to look at something 20 feet away. Additionally,
                    ensuring your screen is at eye level and maintaining a comfortable
                    distance can reduce strain. Using anti-glare screens and proper
                    lighting can further protect your eyes from the harsh blue light
                    emitted by digital devices, potentially reducing the risk of
                    long-term damage.
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
        <div class="accordion-item">
            <h2 class="accordion-header">
                <button class="accordion-button collapsed main-btn fs-4 p-3 rounded"
                        type="button"
                        data-bs-toggle="collapse"
                        data-bs-target="#collapseThree"
                        aria-expanded="false"
                        aria-controls="collapseThree">
                    Lifestyle Choices for Healthy Vision
                </button>
            </h2>
            <div id="collapseThree"
                 class="accordion-collapse collapse"
                 data-bs-parent="#accordionExample">
                <div class="accordion-body">
                    Several lifestyle choices significantly impact eye health,
                    emphasizing the importance of protecting your eyes from external
                    harm. Wearing sunglasses with UV protection shields your eyes from
                    harmful ultraviolet rays, which can cause cataracts and other eye
                    damage over time. Smokers are at higher risk for eye diseases, so
                    quitting smoking can improve overall eye health. Staying hydrated
                    is also crucial, as dehydration can lead to dry eyes.
                    Incorporating regular exercise into your routine can improve
                    circulation, leading to better oxygen and nutrient supply to the
                    eyes, thereby supporting their overall function and health. By
                    making these conscious lifestyle choices, you can significantly
                    enhance and maintain your eye health for years to come.
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>

