                     class="accordion-collapse collapse"
                     aria-labelledby="headingEyeCare"
                     data-bs-parent="#eyeCareAccordion">
                    <div class="accordion-body">
                        One of the most important steps in maintaining good eye health
                        is to have regular eye examinations. These exams help detect
                        vision problems, eye diseases, and other conditions that can
                        lead to vision loss. Early detection and treatment of issues
                        like glaucoma, macular degeneration, and diabetic retinopathy
                        can prevent significant damage. It’s recommended that adults
                        have a comprehensive eye exam every one to two years, depending
                        on age, risk factors, and whether they currently wear glasses or
                        contact lenses.
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="accordion-item">
                <h2 class="accordion-header" id="headingEyeDiseases">
                    <button class="accordion-button collapsed main-btn fs-4 p-3 rounded"
                            type="button"
                            data-bs-toggle="collapse"
                            data-bs-target="#collapseEyeDiseases"
                            aria-expanded="false"
                            aria-controls="collapseEyeDiseases">
                        Healthy Diet and Hydration
                    </button>
                </h2>
                <div id="collapseEyeDiseases"
                     class="accordion-collapse collapse"
                     aria-labelledby="headingEyeDiseases"
                     data-bs-parent="#eyeCareAccordion">
                    <div class="accordion-body">
                        Consuming a diet rich in fruits, vegetables, and omega-3 fatty
                        acids can support eye health. Foods like spinach, kale, and
                        carrots are high in antioxidants such as lutein and zeaxanthin,
                        which help protect the eyes from damage. Omega-3 fatty acids,
                        found in fish like salmon and tuna, are beneficial for
                        maintaining healthy retinal function. Staying hydrated is also
                        crucial as it helps to prevent dry eyes and supports the overall
                        function of the eyes.
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="accordion-item">
                <h2 class="accordion-header" id="headingEyeCauses">
                    <button class="accordion-button collapsed main-btn fs-4 p-3 rounded"
                            type="button"
                            data-bs-toggle="collapse"
                            data-bs-target="#collapseEyeCauses"
                            aria-expanded="false"
                            aria-controls="collapseEyeCauses">
                        Protective Eyewear
                    </button>
                </h2>
                <div id="collapseEyeCauses"
                     class="accordion-collapse collapse"
                     aria-labelledby="headingEyeCauses"
                     data-bs-parent="#eyeCareAccordion">
                    <div class="accordion-body">
                        Wearing sunglasses that block 100% of UVA and UVB rays is
                        essential when outdoors to protect your eyes from harmful
                        ultraviolet light, which can increase the risk of cataracts and
                        macular degeneration. Additionally, wearing protective eyewear
                        during activities that could potentially cause eye injuries,
                        such as sports, home improvement projects, or work that involves
                        hazardous materials, can prevent serious eye damage.
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="accordion-item">
                <h2 class="accordion-header" id="headingEyeAdvice">
                    <button class="accordion-button collapsed main-btn fs-4 p-3 rounded"
                            type="button"
                            data-bs-toggle="collapse"
                            data-bs-target="#collapseEyeAdvice"
                            aria-expanded="false"
                            aria-controls="collapseEyeAdvice">
                        Limit Screen Time and Practice the 20-20-20 Rule
                    </button>
                </h2>
                <div id="collapseEyeAdvice"
                     class="accordion-collapse collapse"
                     aria-labelledby="headingEyeAdvice"
                     data-bs-parent="#eyeCareAccordion">
                    <div class="accordion-body">
                        Prolonged use of computers, smartphones, and other digital
                        devices can lead to digital eye strain, characterized by dry
                        eyes, blurred vision, and headaches. To reduce eye strain,
                        follow the 20-20-20 rule: every 20 minutes, take a 20-second
                        break and look at something 20 feet away. Adjusting your screen
                        to be at eye level, reducing glare with appropriate lighting,
                        and using anti-reflective screen protectors can also help
                        minimize strain on your eyes.
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>

